 Uche Usim, Abuja The Court of Appeal, Abuja Division, has ordered all parties in the committal proceeding instituted against BPE and Mr. Alex A. Okoh, DG, BPE in the matter between BFIG v. BPE to file their brief of argument and other necessary processes before 5th February, 2020 which is the next adjourned date. The Court on Monday, 20th January, 2020, in Appeal number CA/A/117/M/2019, fixed 5th February, 2020 for the hearing of the motion ex-parte or the substantive Appeal. It would be recalled that the Federal High Court, Abuja on 17th December 2019 had ordered that the Director General (DG) BPE be remanded in prison for 30 days for contempt of court. BPE immediately filed an appeal against the judgment of the lower Court and an application for a stay of its execution. In its ruling, the Court of Appeal had ordered the parties to maintain status quo till the next adjourned date of 20th January 2020. 